  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn dappnode, we need a way to set the `monitoring-host` and the UI logs endpoint separately and be able to set `monitoring-host` to 0.0.0.0. Right now we use domains in dappnode, but sometimes we are not able to update the new ip in time, so we get this error:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2020-11-30 14:25:01\" level=error msg=\"Could not listen to host:port :validator.prysm.dappnode:8081: listen tcp 172.33.0.14:8081: bind: cannot assign requested address\" prefix=prometheus\r\n```\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nIt'd be ideal if we could set (even if it's with an environment variable) different endpoints for the `monitoring-host` and where the UI connects to obtain the logs\r\n",
